1
00:00:03,360 --> 00:00:06,699
The first principle to understand 
is that

2
00:00:06,705 --> 00:00:15,509
Madan, Eros, Cupid,
is creating moha, illusion,

3
00:00:15,509 --> 00:00:20,291
and that’s why the illusory world
is being driven by this principle;

4
00:00:20,566 --> 00:00:22,184
[Painfully Beautiful]

5
00:00:22,184 --> 00:00:24,720
it is what makes it spin.

6
00:00:26,012 --> 00:00:31,947
But here Madan is creating
moha for the jīva-souls.

7
00:00:31,947 --> 00:00:35,776
Eros is creating illusion 
for everyone,

8
00:00:35,776 --> 00:00:39,705
it’s the driving principle
of material existence.

9
00:00:39,733 --> 00:00:46,740
Madan Mohan means
Kṛṣṇa is so beautiful,

10
00:00:46,740 --> 00:00:49,767
so seductively charming

11
00:00:49,767 --> 00:00:56,113
that Kṛṣṇa is creating moha,
illusion, for Madan—

12
00:00:56,113 --> 00:01:00,840
Kṛṣṇa is putting Eros
into illusion.

13
00:01:00,840 --> 00:01:06,004
Eros is being seduced
by the Kṛṣṇa conception.

14
00:01:06,004 --> 00:01:10,009
So, as Guru Mahārāj will say
in regard to Mahāprabhu,

15
00:01:10,009 --> 00:01:13,400
koṭi-kāma-mūrchchhitāṅghri-rūpa-rāsa-raṅgaraṁ
[Pds: 2]

16
00:01:13,400 --> 00:01:18,640
Cupids are fainting 
to see the beauty.

17
00:01:19,422 --> 00:01:24,045
hiraṇyāṇāṁ lakṣmī-bharam
abhibhavann āṅgika-ruchā.

18
00:01:24,045 --> 00:01:27,071
Sometimes we use the expression …

19
00:01:27,071 --> 00:01:30,094
In … it’s common usage,
we’d say

20
00:01:30,094 --> 00:01:34,180
someone is painfully beautiful.

21
00:01:34,180 --> 00:01:37,639
You look at them, 
and they’re so beautiful that it goes

22
00:01:37,639 --> 00:01:42,918
that it’s some kind 
of pleasant pain we experience.

23
00:01:42,918 --> 00:01:45,326
You can’t stop
looking at them,

24
00:01:45,326 --> 00:01:47,706
you look away from them
and you want to look back,

25
00:01:47,706 --> 00:01:52,061
but if you look too long
they’re just painfully beautiful.

26
00:01:53,236 --> 00:01:56,980
That’s the type of beauty
that

27
00:01:56,980 --> 00:02:03,211
when Śrīmati Rādhārāṇī’s heart
is enveloping Kṛṣṇa,

28
00:02:03,211 --> 00:02:06,163
He looks so painfully beautiful

29
00:02:06,163 --> 00:02:08,958
that ten million Cupids 
are swooning.

